        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3061757736" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7168330103010374091">Eat less. Eat healthy. That&apos;s basically what Pollan says. Only she uses 152 pages to say it. She could have gotten her points across in a single page, but she provided unnecessary details and constantly restated her points. Beyond redundant, this book is trivial. Pollan wants to convince readers to eat healthy, an honorable goal. However, she provides no science or credibility to her claims, which are based solely on her personal experiences. <br/>From an ecological standpoint, Pollan provides an ima</span>
  <span id="freeText7168330103010374091" style="display:none">Eat less. Eat healthy. That's basically what Pollan says. Only she uses 152 pages to say it. She could have gotten her points across in a single page, but she provided unnecessary details and constantly restated her points. Beyond redundant, this book is trivial. Pollan wants to convince readers to eat healthy, an honorable goal. However, she provides no science or credibility to her claims, which are based solely on her personal experiences. <br />From an ecological standpoint, Pollan provides an image of a fruit or vegetable on nearly every other page. Every other page. It's a huge waste of ink and paper and just makes the book seem longer. Do yourself a favor: don't read the book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7168330103010374091" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


